A: "An expletive  void of sense to fill up the meter"
About: "To a reserved position; half round; in the opposite direction; on the opposite tack; as  to face about; to turn one's self about."
Access: "A paroxysm; a fit of passion; an outburst; as  an access of fury."
Against: "By of before the time that; in preparation for; so as to be ready for the time when."
Although: "Grant all this; be it that; supposing that; notwithstanding; though."
An: "If; -- a word used by old English authors."
Analysis: "The process of ascertaining the name of a species  or its place in a system of classification by means of an analytical table or key."
Apple: "To grow like an apple; to bear apples."
Application: "A request; a document containing a request; as  his application was placed on file."
April: "Fig.: With reference to April being the month in which vegetation begins to put forth  the variableness of its weather etc."
Architectural: "Of or pertaining to the art of building; conformed to the rules of architecture."
Architecture: "Construction  in a more general sense; frame or structure; workmanship."
Are: "The unit of superficial measure  being a square of which each side is ten meters in length; 100 square meters or about 119.6 square yards."
Ark: "A large flatboat used on Western American rivers to transport produce to market."
As: "A Roman copper coin  originally of a pound weight (12 oz.); but reduced after the first Punic war to two ounces; in the second Punic war to one ounce; and afterwards to half an ounce."
Aside: "Something spoken aside; as  a remark made by a stageplayer which the other players are not supposed to hear."
Association: "Union of persons in a company or society for some particular purpose; as  the American Association for the Advancement of Science; a benevolent association. Specifically as among the Congregationalists a society consisting of a number of ministers generally the pastors of neighboring churches united for promoting the interests of religion and the harmony of the churches."
August: "The eighth month of the year  containing thirty-one days."
Base: "To reduce the value of; to debase."
Be: "To signify; to represent or symbolize; to answer to."
Ben: "A hoglike mammal of New Guinea (Porcula papuensis)."
Bill: "To charge or enter in a bill; as  to bill goods."
Brad: "A thin nail  usually small with a slight projection at the top on one side instead of a head; also a small wire nail with a flat circular head; sometimes a small tapering square-bodied finishing nail with a countersunk head."
Bureau: "A chest of drawers for clothes  especially when made as an ornamental piece of furniture."
But: "The hut or shelter of the person who attends to the targets in rifle practice."
By: "Out of the common path; aside; -- used in composition  giving the meaning of something aside secondary or incidental or collateral matter a thing private or avoiding notice; as by-line by-place by-play by-street. It was formerly more freely used in composition than it is now; as by-business by-concernment
Carbon: "An elementary substance  not metallic in its nature which is present in all organic compounds. Atomic weight 11.97. Symbol C. it is combustible and forms the base of lampblack and charcoal and enters largely into mineral coals. In its pure crystallized state it constitutes the diamond the hardest of known substances occuring in monometric crystals like the octahedron etc. Another modification is graphite or blacklead and in this it is soft and occurs in hexagonal prisms or tables. When united with oxygen it forms carbon dioxide commonly called carbonic acid
Carl: "A kind of food. See citation  below."
Change: "Any order in which a number of bells are struck  other than that of the diatonic scale."
Cisco: "The Lake herring (Coregonus Artedi)  valuable food fish of the Great Lakes of North America. The name is also applied to C. Hoyi a related species of Lake Michigan."
Client: "One who consults a legal adviser  or submits his cause to his management."
Cloud: "To grow cloudy; to become obscure with clouds; -- often used with up."
Cocoa: "A preparation made from the seeds of the chocolate tree  and used in making a beverage; also the beverage made from cocoa or cocoa shells."
Code: "Any system of rules or regulations relating to one subject; as  the medical code a system of rules for the regulation of the professional conduct of physicians; the naval code a system of rules for making communications at sea means of signals."
Common: "To board together; to eat at a table in common."
Compliance: "A disposition to yield to others; complaisance."
Conference: "A voluntary association of Congregational churches of a district; the district in which such churches are."
Contact: "The plane between two adjacent bodies of dissimilar rock."
Contemporary: "One who lives at the same time with another; as  Petrarch and Chaucer were contemporaries."
Context: "To knit or bind together; to unite closely."
Contribute: "To give or use one's power or influence for any object; to assist."
Core: "To form by means of a core  as a hole in a casting."
Corporation: "A body politic or corporate  formed and authorized by law to act as a single person and endowed by law with the capacity of succession; a society having the capacity of transacting business as an individual."
Court: "To play the lover; to woo; as  to go courting."
Create: "To invest with a new form  office or character; to constitute; to appoint; to make; as to create one a peer."
Creative: "Having the power to create; exerting the act of creation."
Dean: "The chief or senior of a company on occasion of ceremony; as  the dean of the diplomatic corps; -- so called by courtesy."
December: "Fig.: With reference to the end of the year and to the winter season; as  the December of his life."
Department: "A military subdivision of a country; as  the Department of the Potomac."
Deprecate: "To pray against  as an evil; to seek to avert by prayer; to desire the removal of; to seek deliverance from; to express deep regret for; to disapprove of strongly."
Description: "A class to which a certain representation is applicable; kind; sort."
Designing: "The act of making designs or sketches; the act of forming designs or plans."
Design: "The invention and conduct of the subject; the disposition of every part  and the general order of the whole."
Despite: "In spite of; against  or in defiance of; notwithstanding; as despite his prejudices."
Dictionary: "Hence  a book containing the words belonging to any system or province of knowledge arranged alphabetically; as a dictionary of medicine or of botany; a biographical dictionary."
Digital: "Of or performance to the fingers  or to digits; done with the fingers; as digital compression; digital examination."
Disk: "In owls  the space around the eyes."
Distribution: "The steps or operations by which steam is supplied to and withdrawn from the cylinder at each stroke of the piston; viz.  admission suppression or cutting off release or exhaust and compression of exhaust steam prior to the next admission."
Document: "To furnish with documents or papers necessary to establish facts or give information; as  a a ship should be documented according to the directions of law."
Edit: "To superintend the publication of; to revise and prepare for publication; to select  correct arrange etc. the matter of for publication; as to edit a newspaper."
Em: "The portion of a line formerly occupied by the letter m  then a square type used as a unit by which to measure the amount of printed matter on a page; the square of the body of a type."
Empirical: "Depending upon experience or observation alone  without due regard to science and theory; -- said especially of medical practice remedies etc.; wanting in science and deep insight; as empiric skill remedies."
End: "To come to the ultimate point; to be finished; to come to a close; to cease; to terminate; as  a voyage ends; life ends; winter ends."
Engine: "(Pronounced  in this sense /////.) To rack; to torture."
Engineering: "Originally  the art of managing engines; in its modern and extended sense the art and science by which the mechanical properties of matter are made useful to man in structures and machines; the occupation and work of an engineer."
English: "To strike (the cue ball) in such a manner as to give it in addition to its forward motion a spinning motion  that influences its direction after impact on another ball or the cushion."
Enterprise: "To undertake an enterprise  or something hazardous or difficult."
Evolution: "That series of changes under natural law which involves continuous progress from the homogeneous to the heterogeneous in structure  and from the single and simple to the diverse and manifold in quality or function. The pocess is by some limited to organic beings; by others it is applied to the inorganic and the psychical. It is also applied to explain the existence and growth of institutions manners language civilization and every product of human activity. The agencies and laws of the process are variously explained by different philosophrs."
Extensible: "Capable of being extended  whether in length or breadth; susceptible of enlargement; extensible; extendible; -- the opposite of contractible or compressible."
External: "Something external or without; outward part; that which makes a show  rather than that which is intrinsic; visible form; -- usually in the plural."
Factory: "A building  or collection of buildings appropriated to the manufacture of goods; the place where workmen are employed in fabricating goods wares or utensils; a manufactory; as a cotton factory."
Fall: "That part (as one of the ropes) of a tackle to which the power is applied in hoisting."
February: "The second month in the year  said to have been introduced into the Roman calendar by Numa. In common years this month contains twenty-eight days; in the bissextile or leap year it has twenty-nine days."
Fielding: "The act of playing as a fielder."
First: "The upper part of a duet  trio etc. either vocal or instrumental; -- so called because it generally expresses the air and has a preeminence in the combined effect."
For: "One who takes  or that which is said on the affrimative side; that which is said in favor of some one or something; -- the antithesis of against and commonly used in connection with it."
Forensic: "An exercise in debate; a forensic contest; an argumentative thesis."
form: "A suffix used to denote in the form / shape of  resembling etc.; as valiform; oviform."
Framework: "Work done in  or by means of a frame or loom."
From: "Out of the neighborhood of; lessening or losing proximity to; leaving behind; by reason of; out of; by aid of; -- used whenever departure  setting out commencement of action being state occurrence etc. or procedure emanation absence separation etc.
Front: "To have or turn the face or front in any direction; as  the house fronts toward the east."
Fundamental: "A leading or primary principle  rule law or article which serves as the groundwork of a system; essential part as the fundamentals of the Christian faith."
Further: "To help forward; to promote; to advance; to forward; to help or assist."
Generation: "The aggregate of the functions and phenomene which attend reproduction."
Guava: "A tropical tree  or its fruit of the genus Psidium. Two varieties are well known the P. pyriferum or white guava and P. pomiferum or red guava. The fruit or berry is shaped like a pomegranate but is much smaller. It is somewhat astringent but makes a delicious jelly."
Hybrid: "Produced from the mixture of two species; as  plants of hybrid nature."
We: "The plural nominative case of the pronoun of the first person; the word with which a person in speaking or writing denotes a number or company of which he is one  as the subject of an action expressed by a verb."
In: "To inclose; to take in; to harvest."
Information: "A proceeding in the nature of a prosecution for some offens against the government  instituted and prosecuted really or nominally by some authorized public officer on behalt of the government. It differs from an indictment in criminal cases chiefly in not being based on the finding of a grand juri. See Indictment."
Innovation: "A newly formed shoot  or the annually produced addition to the stems of many mosses."
Institute: "The person to whom an estate is first given by destination or limitation."
Intense: "Extreme in degree; excessive; immoderate; as: (a) Ardent; fervent; as  intense heat. (b) Keen; biting; as intense cold. (c) Vehement; earnest; exceedingly strong; as intense passion or hate. (d) Very severe; violent; as intense pain or anguish. (e) Deep; strong; brilliant; as intense color or light."
Introduction: "A formal and elaborate preliminary treatise; specifically  a treatise introductory to other treatises or to a course of study; a guide; as an introduction to English literature."
Is: "The third person singular of the substantive verb be  in the indicative mood present tense; as he is; he is a man. See Be."
It: "As an indefinite object after some intransitive verbs  or after a substantive used humorously as a verb; as to foot it (i. e. to walk)."
January: "The first month of the year  containing thirty-one days."
Java: "Java coffee  a kind of coffee brought from Java."
Joint: "To fit as if by joints; to coalesce as joints do; as  the stones joint neatly."
Journal: "That portion of a rotating piece  as a shaft axle spindle etc. which turns in a bearing or box. See Illust. of Axle box."
Judge: "To exercise the functions of a magistrate over; to govern."
July: "The seventh month of the year  containing thirty-one days."
Kin: "Of the same nature or kind; kinder."
Language: "To communicate by language; to express in language."
Laura: "A number of hermitages or cells in the same neighborhood occupied by anchorites who were under the same superior."
Legal: "Governed by the rules of law as distinguished from the rules of equity; as  legal estate; legal assets."
License: "To permit or authorize by license; to give license to; as  to license a man to preach."
List: "To engage in public service by enrolling one's name; to enlist."
Log: "To move to and fro; to rock."
Mar: "A mark or blemish made by bruising  scratching or the like; a disfigurement."
March: "A piece of music designed or fitted to accompany and guide the movement of troops; a piece of music in the march form."
Mark: "To take particular notice; to observe critically; to note; to remark."
Market: "To expose for sale in a market; to traffic in; to sell in a market  and in an extended sense to sell in any manner; as most of the farmes have marketed their crops."
Martin: "One of several species of swallows  usually having the tail less deeply forked than the tail of the common swallows."
Method: "Classification; a mode or system of classifying natural objects according to certain common characteristics; as  the method of Theophrastus; the method of Ray; the Linnaean method."
Model: "To make a copy or a pattern; to design or imitate forms; as  to model in wax."
Monolithic: "Of or pertaining to a monolith; consisting of a single stone."
Name: "To designate (a member) by name  as the Speaker does by way of reprimand."
National: "Attached to one's own country or nation."
Network: "Any system of lines or channels interlacing or crossing like the fabric of a net; as  a network of veins; a network of railroads."
Not: "A word used to express negation  prohibition denial or refusal."
November: "The eleventh month of the year  containing thirty days."
October: "Ale or cider made in that month."
On: "In progress; proceeding; as  a game is on."
One: "To cause to become one; to gather into a single whole; to unite; to assimilite."
Only: "Save or except (that); -- an adversative used elliptically with or without that  and properly introducing a single fact or consideration."
Open: "To bark on scent or view of the game."
Opinionated: "Stiff in opinion; firmly or unduly adhering to one's own opinion or to preconceived notions; obstinate in opinion."
Oxford: "Of or pertaining to the city or university of Oxford  England."
Partition: "To divide into distinct parts by lines  walls etc.; as to partition a house."
Pattern: "To serve as an example for; also  to parallel."
Process: "The whole course of proceedings in a cause real or personal  civil or criminal from the beginning to the end of the suit; strictly the means used for bringing the defendant into court to answer to the action; -- a generic term for writs of the class called judicial."
Proprietary: "Belonging  or pertaining to a proprietor; considered as property; owned; as proprietary medicine."
Protection: "A theory  or a policy of protecting the producers in a country from foreign competition in the home market by the imposition of such discriminating duties on goods of foreign production as will restrict or prevent their importation; -- opposed to free trade."
Protocol: "To make or write protocols  or first draughts; to issue protocols."
Recent: "Of or pertaining to the present or existing epoch; as  recent shells."
Release: "The act of opening the exhaust port to allow the steam to escape."
Request: "To address with a request; to ask."
Resource: "Pecuniary means; funds; money  or any property that can be converted into supplies; available means or capabilities of any kind."
Review: "A lesson studied or recited for a second time."
Revival: "Revivification  as of a metal. See Revivification 2."
Rump: "The hind or tail end; a fag-end; a remnant."
Scala: "A term applied to any one of the three canals of the cochlea."
Scaling: "Serving as an aid in clambering; as  a scaling ladder used in assaulting a fortified place."
School: "To tutor; to chide and admonish; to reprove; to subject to systematic discipline; to train."
Search: "The act of seeking or looking for something; quest; inquiry; pursuit for finding something; examination."
See: "To be attentive; to take care; to give heed; -- generally with to; as  to see to the house."
Segmentation: "The act or process of dividing into segments; specifically (Biol.)  a self-division into segments as a result of growth; cell cleavage; cell multiplication; endogenous cell formation."
September: "The ninth month of the year  containing thurty days."
Service: "Act of serving or covering. See Serve  v. t. 13."
Shell: "To be disengaged from the ear or husk; as  wheat or rye shells in reaping."
Sheth: "The part of a plow which projects downward beneath the beam  for holding the share and other working parts; -- also called standard or post."
Social: "Forming compound groups or colonies by budding from basal processes or stolons; as  the social ascidians."
Some: "A part; a portion; -- used pronominally  and followed sometimes by of; as some of our provisions."
Standard: "Not of the dwarf kind; as  a standard pear tree."
Statistics: "The branch of mathematics which studies methods for the calculation of probabilities."
Steve: "To pack or stow  as cargo in a ship's hold. See Steeve."
Steven: "An outcry; a loud call; a clamor."
Storage: "The price changed for keeping goods in a store."
Structured: "Having a definite organic structure; showing differentiation of parts."
Study: "To make an object of study; to aim at sedulously; to devote one's thoughts to; as  to study the welfare of others; to study variety in composition."
Sun: "To expose to the sun's rays; to warm or dry in the sun; as  to sun cloth; to sun grain."
Supreme: "Situated at the highest part or point."
System: "One of the stellate or irregular clusters of intimately united zooids which are imbedded in  or scattered over the surface of the common tissue of many compound ascidians."
Technology: "Industrial science; the science of systematic knowledge of the industrial arts  especially of the more important manufactures as spinning weaving metallurgy etc."
Text: "To write in large characters  as in text hand."
The: "By that; by how much; by so much; on that account; -- used before comparatives; as  the longer we continue in sin the more difficult it is to reform."
This: "As an adjective  this has the same demonstrative force as the pronoun but is followed by a noun; as this book; this way to town."
Thread: "To form a thread  or spiral rib on or in; as to thread a screw or nut."
To: "Character; condition of being; purpose subserved or office filled."
Toggle: "Two rods or plates connected by a toggle joint."
Traditional: "Observant of tradition; attached to old customs; old-fashioned."
Transfer: "A pathological process by virtue of which a unilateral morbid condition on being abolished on one side of the body makes its appearance in the corresponding region upon the other side."
Twitter: "A slight trembling or agitation of the nerves."
University: "An institution organized and incorporated for the purpose of imparting instruction  examining students and otherwise promoting education in the higher branches of literature science art etc. empowered to confer degrees in the several arts and faculties as in theology law medicine music etc. A university may exist without having any college connected with it
Use: "To be accustomed to go; to frequent; to inhabit; to dwell; -- sometimes followed by of."
Van: "To fan  or to cleanse by fanning; to winnow."
Venture: "To confide in; to rely on; to trust."
Virtual: "Being in essence or effect  not in fact; as the virtual presence of a man in his agent or substitute."
Web: "To unite or surround with a web  or as if with a web; to envelop; to entangle."
What: "Why? For what purpose? On what account?"
When: "Which time; then; -- used elliptically as a noun."
Whereas: "When in fact; while on the contrary; the case being in truth that; although; -- implying opposition to something that precedes; or implying recognition of facts  sometimes followed by a different statement and sometimes by inferences or something consequent."
Which: "A compound relative or indefinite pronoun  standing for any one which whichever that which those which the . . . which and the like; as take which you will."
With: "To denote having as a possession or an appendage; as  the firmament with its stars; a bride with a large fortune."
Without: "Outside of the house; out of doors."
Workshop: "A shop where any manufacture or handiwork is carried on."
